<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="626" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114A European War 1939/102:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Childs</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-10T22:00:00+01:00">November
                                    10, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 10—3:56 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>584. The 19 American aviators and soldiers mentioned in my 582 of
                            November 10 landed at the air drome in Tetuán early on November 8 after
                            losing their way and running short of petrol. They were forced off their
                            course by AA fire. Their plane was landed in perfect condition and is
                            now under guard of the Spanish authorities.</p>
                        <p>The Lieutenant in command informed me privately that it was his
                            understanding that he was not to destroy his instruments in a neutral
                            country and unfortunately he had not undertaken this. The plane is a
                            troop carrier.</p>
                        <p>Please instruct urgently what representations if any I should make
                            concerning the status of this plane.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Childs</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>